p><p> In other Jerry Cantrell news, last month the guitarist got fans talking when he revealed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/alice-in-chains-jerry-cantrell-has-talked-to-metallicas-james-hetfield-about-making-music-together-and-jammed-3826777">he and Metallica frontman James Hetfield have spoken about making music together</a> .</p><p> “James and I have talked about it, kind of… We never had a formal conversation but I&#39;ve jammed with him at Kirk&#39;s [Hammett, Metallica guitarist] place,” he said.</p><p> “It&#39;s something I&#39;d be really curious about – even to just write a song with him. As for whether it&#39;d turn into something more than that… he&#39;s got a pretty demanding day job. So I&#39;d understand if it never comes to be.”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-alice-in-chains-jerry-cantrell-perform-hate-to-feel-first-time-over-30-years-3834537">Watch Alice In Chains&#39; Jerry Cantrell perform &#39;Hate To Feel&#39; for first time in over three decades</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
